In just five weeks, more than 4 million Ukrainian children have fled their homes – that’s one every second since the war began. The families who've stayed in Ukraine are facing danger every day.
 
I recently spoke with UNICEF spokesperson James Elder who’s been on the ground in Ukraine to hear what's happening for children and families and what UNICEF teams are doing to help.
 
The situation is dire, but donations to UNICEF are reaching children in need. You can help today by donating via the link in my bio.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Climate Action
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
The last decade has been Australia hottest in the last century. It will also most likely be the coolest decade in the next century.

No athlete, whether an elite professional or a community player, is immune to our increasingly hot summers, which are a health hazard for those playing and watching sport.

Let’s work together to tackle Climate Change. 

Find out more www.climatecouncil.org.au
@theclimatecouncil
